         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12/8/90 ¶  ¶ Let me offer my best felicitation, dear Mr Baker, to your promotion, so well earned. ¶  Yours must be a very happy existence, all the more as you have a young talented son in the bot. Dep...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">90.08.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Baker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Letters to J. G. Baker, f. 65.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Date stamped: </seg>Royal Gardens Kew 22. Sep. 90.</p>
               </note>12/8/90</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me offer my best felicitation, dear Mr Baker, to your promotion, so well earned.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">John Baker was promoted from Principal Assistant to Keeper of the Herbarium and Library upon the resignation of Professor Daniel Oliver (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gardeners’ chronicle</seg>, 21 June 1890, p. 770).</p>
               </note> Yours must be a very happy existence, all the more as you have a young talented son in the bot. Department of the British Museum,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Edmund Baker.</p>
               </note> who can cooperate to some extent with you, and whom you can further guide in his career. </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
